# Investigating Phishing Emails through CyberChef & VirusTotal
##Documentation

This folder contains the coursework created throughout the semester for the project " Investigating Phishing Emails through CyberChef & VirusTotal" in BFOR 643.

The "README.md" file, it illustrates the development process of the project and the investigation workflow to analysis techniques and evidence collection, all of which directly support the final results.

---
##Project Overview & Scope

BFOR643 - Title, Scope, and Team Members
Defines the purpose of the project, which is to investigate a phishing email sampled from GitHub. We were able to outline the problem being addressed, identify and analyze phishing threats using CyberChef and VirusTotal.

BFOR 643 - Overview of the Project
Highlights the relevance of the phishing investigation, including identifying Indicators of Compromise(IOCs), decoding hidden content(CyberChef), and verifying threats(VirusTotal). It also explains how the project simulates a real-world incident response scenario in a controlled environment. Expected outcomes from this project includes improvement with threat detection skills, awareness of phishing techniques and stronger incident response practices.

---
##Data Analysis & Investigation Flow
Explains the step-by-step analysis process, including:

* Extracting and reviewing email headers.
* Identifying suspicious sender details and authentication failures (SPF, DKIM, DMARC).
* Decoding embedded content using CyberChef (e.g., Base64 decoding).
* Extracting URLs, domains, and IP addresses.
* Verifying IOCs using VirusTotal.

This workflow demonstrates how raw email data is transformed into actionable threat intelligence and supports evidence-based conclusions.

